default13. 
defaultOur f
defaultormative research showed that Palestinians are 
defaultinterested in issues that affect the running of their daily lives, whether
default 
defaulthealth service delivery, employment, emigration or domestic violence. 
defaultThe 
defaultVoices of Palestine
default programme on domestic violence and sexual harassment
default, for example,
default took place at the po
defaultlice college in Jericho
default. The panel
default included 
defaulta
default female police officer responsible for domestic violence &amp; sexual harassment issues, a female criminologist from the Hebrew University in Jerusalem and the Head of the Sharia Courts. The audience contained 
defaultboth 
defaultmen and women with a strong representation of police cadets. There wa
defaults
default a very lively debate about the appropriateness of women’s 
defaultdress
default;
default with female participants making it clear that sexual harassment was unacceptable 
defaultregardless of clothing choices women ma
defaulty make
default. 
default14. 
defaultThe 
defaultHur El Kalam
default programme on the provision of health services raised a num
defaultber of issues concerning health care 
defaultrationing
default. There was heated debate over 
defaultwhy some patients 
defaultwere allowed to die from critical illness rather than getting treatment, 
defaultparticularly 
defaultwhen it was clear that 
defaultsome
default hospitals in Israel and Jordan would be willing to carry out the surgery. There was 
defaultalso 
defaulta strong discussion on why the PA did not do more to punish people who sold 
defaultcounterfeit
default 
defaultor out-of-
defaultdate drugs. The most harrowi
defaultng part of the programme was when a man described losing his wife to medical negligence
default, 
defaultsaying that he felt helpless because there was no mechanism 
defaultto r
defaultedress he failings he had experienced
default in the health system
default. 
defaultThe Health Minister pledged on the programm
defaulte to review this gentleman’s case and take action if warranted.
