defaultConclusions and defaultRecommendations:default21. 
defaultThe media is a potentially powerful tool in 
defaultenabling 
defaulta peaceful, inclusive, accountable OPT
default, with 
defaultmore than 85% of those watching BBC Media Action-supported debate progra
defaultmmes believing that the shows are playing a role in holding government to account
default. 
default22. 
defaultBBC Media Action’s needs analysis shows that participatory media formats that engage 
defaultpeople  
defaultand politicians alike on issues of everyday service delivery are both 
defaultdemanded – and feasible – in OPT.
default23. 
defaultDue to the particular characteristics of Palestinian demographic, economic and social divisions, as well as the importance of the Palestinian diaspora, the internet provides a unique platform for communication and
default enga
defaultgement
default. 
defaultSocial media
default helps reduce offline boundaries and offset the lack of mobility in the territories and beyond
default, while also drawing in youth audiences.
default24. 
defaultNearly one third of Palestinian youth surveyed by BBC Media Action reported using social media at
default least once to engage in public affairs. In a 
defaultterritory 
defaultwhere nearly 2/3 of the entire population is under the age of 25, 
defaultschools and universities alike should be encouraged to develop 
defaultcurricula 
defaultthat 
defaultteach 
defaultmedia literac
defaulty so that students learn to use socia
defaultl media tools in a responsible manner and in support of a public purpose. 
default2
default5
default. 
defaultLocal media might also consider experimenting with n
defaulton
default-
defaulttraditional forms of media that 
defaultcan stimulate discussion and debate on governance in the OPT. 
defaultProgramming 
defaultfrom elsewhere 
defaultsuggests that drama series, game shows, quizzes and 
defaultsatire
default can also play a role in 
defaultholding
default 
defaultleaders 
defaultgovernment
defaults
default 
defaultto account.
default26
default. 
defaultGovernment agencies should be encouraged to
default 
defaultactively encourage and provide opportunities for citizens to express opinions,
default 
defaultask qu
defaultestions and receive a credible response. 
defaultGovernment departments in the OPT should promote services more effectively, accept public criticism of those services and take part in relevant media programming that enables citizens to express opinions, ask questi
defaultons and receive a credible response. 
default27. 
defaultThe emerging ﬁeld of mGovernance 
defaultelsewhere in the developing world 
defaultoffers a particularly compelling example in this regard. On the supply side, mobile phones are being used to provide people with basic information 
defaultabout local and national politics via SMS and voice-based communication software. On the demand side, even quite basic mobile phones are being used for accountability ends as diverse as monitoring elections, improving service delivery and tackling corrupti
defaulton at the local level.
